      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Research by economists such as George Borjas and Gordon Hanson has shown that while immigration can lead to short-term wage gains for low-skilled workers, it can also lead to long-term wage stagnation for native-born workers, particularly in areas with high levels of unemployment. However, this effect is often overstated and exaggerated by critics of immigration, who fail to account for the overall economic benefits of immigration and the fact that many native-born workers are willing to work for lower wages.",
